WEBVTT

1
00:06:08.550 --> 00:06:10.176
Alert the queen.

2
00:06:29.946 --> 00:06:31.156
Hyah!

3
00:09:00.763 --> 00:09:03.725
Bruce Vayne.

4
00:09:03.808 --> 00:09:05.476
Bruce Wayne.

5
00:09:23.286 --> 00:09:24.829
Talk.

6
00:09:26.122 --> 00:09:27.749
I believe there is a stranger.

7
00:09:27.832 --> 00:09:30.543
Comes to this village
from the sea.

8
00:09:30.627 --> 00:09:33.713
He comes in the winter
when the people are hungry.

9
00:09:33.796 --> 00:09:36.007
He brings fish.

10
00:09:36.132 --> 00:09:37.842
He comes on the king tide.

11
00:09:37.967 --> 00:09:39.052
That was last night.

12
00:09:45.600 --> 00:09:48.061
You have eyes. so see.

13
00:09:48.102 --> 00:09:49.771
Icebergs in the harbor.

14
00:09:49.896 --> 00:09:52.899
It's four months since
the last ship got through.

15
00:09:52.982 --> 00:09:57.445
Well. this stranger
doesn't come by ship.

16
00:10:03.993 --> 00:10:07.914
There are enemies
coming from far away.

17
00:10:09.123 --> 00:10:10.750
I need warriors.

18
00:10:10.792 --> 00:10:14.504
This stranger. others like him.

19
00:10:14.629 --> 00:10:18.841
I'm building an alliance
to defend ourselves.

20
00:10:18.967 --> 00:10:22.262
It's very important
that I see this man.

21
00:10:23.221 --> 00:10:25.431
If this stranger exists.

22
00:10:25.556 --> 00:10:27.850
he'll give him your message.

23
00:10:27.976 --> 00:10:29.185
$5.000 American.

24
00:10:29.310 --> 00:10:30.937
Look. I'll give you $25.000

25
00:10:30.979 --> 00:10:34.148
to talk to this man
right now. outside.

26
00:10:45.910 --> 00:10:51.165
How dare this dog
speak to us like children.

27
00:10:51.332 --> 00:10:55.003
Ooh. magical man from the sea.

28
00:10:55.169 --> 00:10:58.047
We are poor. not stupid.

29
00:10:58.172 --> 00:10:59.882
Get out.

30
00:11:01.050 --> 00:11:02.468
I'm sorry.

31
00:11:02.510 --> 00:11:04.303
Can't do that.

32
00:11:04.387 --> 00:11:06.681
I'll leave after we've spoken.

33
00:11:11.352 --> 00:11:12.812
He said. "Get out."

34
00:11:31.873 --> 00:11:33.624
Arthur Curry.

35
00:11:33.750 --> 00:11:36.711
Also known as
Protector of the Oceans.

36
00:11:37.295 --> 00:11:38.963
The Aquaman.

37
00:11:44.552 --> 00:11:46.179
So. let me get this straight.

38
00:11:46.220 --> 00:11:50.058
You do it dressed like a bat?
Like an actual bat?

39
00:11:50.224 --> 00:11:51.976
Worked for 20 years in Gotham.

40
00:11:52.101 --> 00:11:53.728
Oh. that shithole.

41
00:11:53.895 --> 00:11:55.730
When the fight comes.
we'll need you.

42
00:11:55.855 --> 00:11:58.274
- Don't count on it. Batman.
- Why not?

43
00:11:58.399 --> 00:12:00.586
{\an5}'Cause I don't like you coming
here. digging into my business

44
00:12:00.610 --> 00:12:03.237
and getting into my life.
I want to be left alone.

45
00:12:03.363 --> 00:12:04.947
Is that why you do this?

46
00:12:05.073 --> 00:12:06.675
Why you help these people out
here in the middle of nowhere?

47
00:12:06.699 --> 00:12:07.909
I've read the stories.

48
00:12:08.034 --> 00:12:10.286
Your good deeds
you think no one sees.

49
00:12:10.411 --> 00:12:11.788
You'll join us.

50
00:12:11.913 --> 00:12:13.915
"Strong man
is strongest alone."

51
00:12:13.998 --> 00:12:15.458
You ever heard that?

52
00:12:15.583 --> 00:12:17.043
You ever hear of Superman?

53
00:12:17.168 --> 00:12:18.795
He died fighting next to me.

54
00:12:20.088 --> 00:12:21.422
My point exactly.

55
00:12:21.589 --> 00:12:23.883
He believed
we were stronger together.

56
00:12:23.966 --> 00:12:25.510
We owe it to him.

57
00:12:25.635 --> 00:12:27.970
I don't owe anyone anything.

58
00:12:35.520 --> 00:12:38.272
Dressed like a bat.

59
00:12:38.356 --> 00:12:40.399
You're out of your mind.
Bruce Wayne.

60
00:14:08.696 --> 00:14:10.031
Move over. Dusty.

61
00:15:05.795 --> 00:15:08.881
My God. Master Wayne.
but this is cold.

62
00:15:08.923 --> 00:15:13.469
Maybe we can catch
the next king tide in Jamaica?

63
00:15:13.594 --> 00:15:15.805
Might be
a metahuman or two in Fiji.

64
00:15:15.930 --> 00:15:17.598
Costa Rica's nice.

65
00:15:17.765 --> 00:15:19.267
I found him.

66
00:15:22.186 --> 00:15:24.272
He said no.

67
00:15:24.355 --> 00:15:26.774
So the draft stands
at naught for two?

68
00:15:28.985 --> 00:15:31.779
Maybe a man who broods
in a cave for a living

69
00:15:31.946 --> 00:15:35.658
isn't cut out to be
a recruiter. Hmm?

70
00:15:55.303 --> 00:15:57.013
That's $10. please.

71
00:16:01.684 --> 00:16:06.355
<i>Let us go now</i>

72
00:16:06.480 --> 00:16:13.613
<i>My darling companion</i>

73
00:16:20.494 --> 00:16:24.832
<i>Set out for the</i>

74
00:16:26.167 --> 00:16:33.174
<i>Distant skies...</i>

75
00:16:35.259 --> 00:16:36.260
Good morning. Miss Lane.

76
00:16:36.385 --> 00:16:37.762
Jerry. hi.

77
00:16:38.512 --> 00:16:40.431
Wow.

78
00:16:40.556 --> 00:16:41.891
You don't miss a day. do you?

79
00:16:43.309 --> 00:16:45.186
Like it here.

80
00:16:50.941 --> 00:16:58.074
<i>They told us our gods
would outlive us</i>

81
00:16:58.199 --> 00:17:04.246
<i>They told us our dreams
would outlive us</i>

82
00:17:06.582 --> 00:17:13.047
<i>They told us our gods
would outlive us</i>

83
00:17:14.423 --> 00:17:20.388
<i>But they lied</i>

84
00:18:30.708 --> 00:18:31.792
Excuse me.

85
00:18:33.085 --> 00:18:34.462
Move!

86
00:18:45.139 --> 00:18:46.849
Move it! Move it!

87
00:18:52.897 --> 00:18:55.608
- No. mate. don't shoot!
- Move. move!

88
00:18:55.691 --> 00:18:57.318
Get the fuck over there!

89
00:18:59.320 --> 00:19:00.946
Move! All of ya!

90
00:19:11.290 --> 00:19:13.459
Line them up along the wall.

91
00:19:13.542 --> 00:19:16.170
Keep them quiet.

92
00:19:16.295 --> 00:19:18.756
- Keep quiet!
- Shut up! Shut up!

93
00:19:18.881 --> 00:19:20.341
Shut them up too!

94
00:19:23.219 --> 00:19:25.888
We'll be making
a statement shortly.

95
00:19:26.013 --> 00:19:27.890
Until then.
if I see any movement.

96
00:19:28.015 --> 00:19:30.142
you'll have a lot of dead kids
on your hands.

97
00:19:45.032 --> 00:19:46.659
Should I take him?

98
00:19:46.742 --> 00:19:48.410
Hold your fire.

99
00:19:49.870 --> 00:19:51.080
They've got kids in there.

100
00:19:52.915 --> 00:19:54.750
Yeah. he's not bluffing. chief.

101
00:19:54.875 --> 00:19:57.169
St. Brigid's had
a school trip today.

102
00:20:21.110 --> 00:20:22.903
Quiet! Shut up!

103
00:20:27.992 --> 00:20:30.452
Down with the modern world.

104
00:20:30.578 --> 00:20:32.162
Back to the Dark Ages.

105
00:20:37.585 --> 00:20:38.585
Quiet!

106
00:20:40.421 --> 00:20:43.257
I said shut your fucking mouth.

107
00:20:56.228 --> 00:20:59.064
Who are you?

108
00:20:59.106 --> 00:21:02.151
The Lasso of Hestia compels
you to reveal the truth.

109
00:21:02.776 --> 00:21:04.653
Now. who are you?

110
00:21:04.778 --> 00:21:07.990
We're a small group
of reactionary terrorists

111
00:21:08.115 --> 00:21:09.635
who wanna turn back
the clock in Europe

112
00:21:09.700 --> 00:21:12.119
- a thousand years.
- Boring. Why the hostages?

113
00:21:12.286 --> 00:21:13.787
We have no demands.

114
00:21:13.871 --> 00:21:15.789
We're just stalling the police
while we do it.

115
00:21:15.873 --> 00:21:17.333
While you do what?

116
00:21:17.458 --> 00:21:21.462
You're too late.
The countdown's already begun.

117
00:21:21.545 --> 00:21:25.090
In a few minutes.
four city blocks...

118
00:21:26.383 --> 00:21:29.470
while the world watches.

119
00:23:09.069 --> 00:23:10.237
No!

120
00:23:10.362 --> 00:23:12.281
Like lambs to the slaughter.

121
00:24:00.871 --> 00:24:02.956
I don't believe it.

122
00:24:03.081 --> 00:24:04.249
Believe it.

123
00:24:39.576 --> 00:24:42.704
Is everyone all right?
Are you okay?

124
00:24:42.830 --> 00:24:44.790
Good. It's okay.

125
00:24:44.832 --> 00:24:47.167
It's okay. It's over.
You can stand up.

126
00:24:47.292 --> 00:24:48.502
It's all good.

127
00:24:48.669 --> 00:24:50.712
It's over now.
Are you okay?

128
00:24:50.838 --> 00:24:52.881
You okay? Good.

129
00:24:58.470 --> 00:24:59.847
Are you okay. princess?

130
00:25:03.225 --> 00:25:05.227
Can I be like you someday?

131
00:25:07.229 --> 00:25:09.857
You can be anything
you want to be.

132
00:25:11.859 --> 00:25:14.278
Come on. Let's go.

133
00:25:56.987 --> 00:25:58.196
Any changes today?

134
00:25:58.238 --> 00:25:59.823
No. my Queen.

135
00:26:01.450 --> 00:26:03.368
The Mother Box has awoken.

136
00:26:03.452 --> 00:26:06.455
yet nothing has happened.

137
00:26:06.580 --> 00:26:08.832
It has slept
for thousands of years

138
00:26:08.957 --> 00:26:10.918
since the First Age.

139
00:26:11.043 --> 00:26:12.419
Why did it wake at all?

140
00:26:20.010 --> 00:26:22.054
This is the first time
it's gone quiet

141
00:26:22.137 --> 00:26:23.388
since the crack appeared.

142
00:26:23.430 --> 00:26:26.350
Maybe it's going back to sleep.

143
00:26:30.312 --> 00:26:32.231
Evil does not sleep.

144
00:26:32.981 --> 00:26:34.942
It waits.

145
00:26:36.318 --> 00:26:38.445
Something is coming.

146
00:26:43.492 --> 00:26:44.993
Prepare for battle!

147
00:27:10.852 --> 00:27:13.188
Amazons. on your marks!

148
00:27:13.313 --> 00:27:14.690
Ready!

149
00:27:39.923 --> 00:27:41.883
Defenders.

150
00:27:43.468 --> 00:27:48.140
They have failed 100.000 worlds.

151
00:27:48.223 --> 00:27:49.808
They always fail.

152
00:27:51.643 --> 00:27:56.398
I've come to enlighten you
to the great darkness.

153
00:27:56.523 --> 00:27:59.568
I will bathe in your fear.

154
00:28:01.069 --> 00:28:03.572
Daughters of Themyscira.

155
00:28:04.698 --> 00:28:06.324
show him your fear!

156
00:28:06.450 --> 00:28:08.952
We have no fear!

157
00:28:28.263 --> 00:28:29.890
Gather the legions!

158
00:28:30.891 --> 00:28:32.017
Go with her!

159
00:28:32.100 --> 00:28:33.393
You must seal the cage!

160
00:28:33.560 --> 00:28:35.854
- Go!
- Phillipus!

161
00:29:02.464 --> 00:29:03.757
No!

162
00:29:16.269 --> 00:29:17.479
Behind you!

163
00:29:21.274 --> 00:29:22.651
Ahhh!

164
00:29:24.861 --> 00:29:25.946
Epione.

165
00:29:27.739 --> 00:29:29.950
Honor us. It's right.

166
00:29:32.953 --> 00:29:34.162
Seal it.

167
00:29:39.459 --> 00:29:42.087
Ready the hammers!

168
00:29:54.349 --> 00:29:56.435
Seal it now!

169
00:31:30.779 --> 00:31:32.322
Guard it with your life.

170
00:31:32.447 --> 00:31:34.407
- Yes. my Queen.
- Keep it moving.

171
00:31:34.491 --> 00:31:35.951
Hyah! Hyah!

172
00:32:59.075 --> 00:33:01.077
Hyah!

173
00:34:20.532 --> 00:34:22.117
Got it! Go!

174
00:34:23.243 --> 00:34:24.536
Hyah!

175
00:34:44.848 --> 00:34:49.185
Oh. noble Queen.
Why do you fight?

176
00:34:52.105 --> 00:34:53.940
You can't save her.

177
00:34:54.023 --> 00:34:56.776
You can't save any of them.

178
00:34:59.946 --> 00:35:04.075
The great darkness begins.

179
00:35:04.117 --> 00:35:05.910
Amazons!

180
00:35:16.129 --> 00:35:18.965
Yes. we will find the others.

181
00:35:20.759 --> 00:35:23.303
Draw!

182
00:35:25.472 --> 00:35:26.806
Loose!

183
00:36:24.697 --> 00:36:26.658
He's gone back to his universe.

184
00:36:26.741 --> 00:36:27.909
No.

185
00:36:30.245 --> 00:36:32.747
He's gone to the lands of men

186
00:36:32.872 --> 00:36:36.042
to find the other two boxes.

187
00:36:36.125 --> 00:36:39.212
We have to light
the ancient warning fire.

188
00:36:39.295 --> 00:36:42.882
The fire has not burned
for 5.000 years.

189
00:36:43.007 --> 00:36:44.551
Men won't know what it means.

190
00:36:45.468 --> 00:36:46.970
Men won't.

191
00:36:48.596 --> 00:36:50.098
She will.

192
00:37:20.753 --> 00:37:23.423
It's toxic.

193
00:37:23.590 --> 00:37:25.300
That's good.

194
00:37:46.279 --> 00:37:47.279
Go!

195
00:37:47.363 --> 00:37:49.616
Follow the scent
of the Mother Boxes.

196
00:37:49.741 --> 00:37:51.200
Find the missing two.

197
00:37:51.326 --> 00:37:55.246
Once they are found.
The Unity will be formed.

198
00:37:55.330 --> 00:37:58.291
This world will join the others.

199
00:38:00.043 --> 00:38:02.128
He will be pleased.

200
00:38:02.211 --> 00:38:05.298
He will see my worth again.

201
00:38:07.884 --> 00:38:09.510
Hey.

202
00:38:09.636 --> 00:38:12.513
Anything on that kid
from the liquor store?

203
00:38:12.639 --> 00:38:14.140
Possibly.

204
00:38:14.807 --> 00:38:16.976
"Possibly."

205
00:38:17.101 --> 00:38:19.520
If I had a dollar
for every "possibly."

206
00:38:19.646 --> 00:38:22.523
Yeah. it would make you
even more insufferable.

207
00:38:25.360 --> 00:38:28.154
Facial scan might have
got a hit on him.

208
00:38:28.237 --> 00:38:30.490
our disappearing man.

209
00:38:30.615 --> 00:38:35.370
One Mr. Barry Allen
from Central City.

210
00:38:35.495 --> 00:38:36.996
Might be another false positive.

211
00:38:37.121 --> 00:38:38.515
you'll have to give me
a little time

212
00:38:38.539 --> 00:38:41.125
- to confirm.
- We don't have any more time.

213
00:38:42.669 --> 00:38:44.295
Master Wayne.

214
00:38:44.420 --> 00:38:46.881
you've been working
as if there's no tomorrow

215
00:38:47.006 --> 00:38:48.091
to build this team

216
00:38:48.216 --> 00:38:50.093
of people you can't even find.

217
00:38:50.218 --> 00:38:52.345
I found one.
I found two. including Diana.

218
00:38:52.428 --> 00:38:54.472
Just because Lex Luthor says

219
00:38:54.555 --> 00:38:56.432
the planet's
in danger of attack?

220
00:38:56.557 --> 00:38:58.726
This has nothing
to do with Lex Luthor.

221
00:38:58.851 --> 00:39:00.186
It has to do with him.

222
00:39:00.269 --> 00:39:04.315
I made a promise to him
on his grave.

223
00:39:04.399 --> 00:39:07.527
I spent a lot of time
trying to divide us.

224
00:39:07.652 --> 00:39:11.197
I need to bring us together
and make this right.

225
00:39:11.322 --> 00:39:14.033
Well. it's been some time
since Luthor's warning.

226
00:39:14.200 --> 00:39:18.371
No attacks.
No barbarians at the gate.

227
00:39:18.496 --> 00:39:22.000
Maybe these barbarians
don't use a gate.

228
00:39:22.083 --> 00:39:23.751
Maybe they're already here.

229
00:39:27.630 --> 00:39:29.549
Keep looking.
What else do you have?

230
00:40:08.463 --> 00:40:10.047
Lab's all yours. Howard.

231
00:40:10.173 --> 00:40:11.924
11:30.

232
00:40:12.008 --> 00:40:13.509
Early night for you. Silas.

233
00:40:13.634 --> 00:40:16.095
Yes. early night.

234
00:40:16.220 --> 00:40:17.430
Tell your family I said hello.

235
00:40:52.840 --> 00:40:54.467
What the...

236
00:40:58.179 --> 00:40:59.305
Jesus.

237
00:42:12.587 --> 00:42:15.381
The Arrow of Artemis.

238
00:42:15.506 --> 00:42:18.259
It will reach the lands of men.

239
00:42:27.810 --> 00:42:29.061
Sky torch.

240
00:42:29.228 --> 00:42:30.897
hero beacon.

241
00:42:30.980 --> 00:42:32.523
scatter the darkness.

242
00:42:32.648 --> 00:42:36.235
Burn as you burned
in days before.

243
00:42:37.570 --> 00:42:41.407
Show her the darkness before
the daylight of history.

244
00:42:41.532 --> 00:42:45.369
Warn my daughter
that war has come

245
00:42:46.704 --> 00:42:48.414
and protect her.

246
00:43:13.022 --> 00:43:15.441
Return to me. Diana.

247
00:43:53.813 --> 00:43:55.335
<i>What did you do</i>

248
00:43:55.336 --> 00:43:56.857
<i>this weekend. Diana?</i>

249
00:43:56.983 --> 00:43:58.943
Nothing very interesting.

250
00:43:59.068 --> 00:44:01.737
That's all you ever tell us.

251
00:44:01.862 --> 00:44:05.241
What can I do?
I'm not that exciting.

252
00:44:05.366 --> 00:44:09.537
You might as well disappear
when you walk out of here.

253
00:44:14.041 --> 00:44:15.042
Again?

254
00:44:15.167 --> 00:44:17.253
- What is it?
- Now what?

255
00:44:17.378 --> 00:44:20.506
Budget cuts. tomb raiders.

256
00:44:20.589 --> 00:44:23.342
Now add to the list "arson."

257
00:44:24.885 --> 00:44:26.637
<i>Yes. good morning</i>

258
00:44:26.762 --> 00:44:28.222
<i>From the isle of Crete.</i>

259
00:44:28.347 --> 00:44:29.849
<i>As you can see behind me.</i>

260
00:44:29.932 --> 00:44:32.184
<i>an enormous bonfire is burning.</i>

261
00:44:32.310 --> 00:44:34.645
<i>This fire has been burning
through the night.</i>

262
00:44:34.729 --> 00:44:36.063
<i>We're now into the morning</i>

263
00:44:36.188 --> 00:44:38.566
<i>and we are
at least five miles away.</i>

264
00:44:38.691 --> 00:44:41.986
<i>And we can still
see it burning as we speak.</i>

265
00:44:42.069 --> 00:44:45.364
<i>This has baffled locals and
government authorities alike</i>

266
00:44:45.489 --> 00:44:47.324
<i>here at this historical site</i>

267
00:44:47.408 --> 00:44:49.869
<i>of the so-called shrine
of the Amazons.</i>

268
00:44:50.036 --> 00:44:51.888
<i>Now. locals and government
officials are baffled as to</i>

269
00:44:51.912 --> 00:44:54.331
<i>- what may have caused this.</i>
- Invasion.

270
00:45:03.257 --> 00:45:04.383
Ryan.

271
00:45:04.508 --> 00:45:05.760
- Hiya. Doc.
- Is the...

272
00:45:05.885 --> 00:45:07.887
No damage to the electron-laser.

273
00:45:08.012 --> 00:45:10.264
- Uh. Dr. Silas Stone?
- Yeah.

274
00:45:10.389 --> 00:45:12.224
- Ryan Choi?
- That's us.

275
00:45:12.350 --> 00:45:14.560
Um. who did this?
Did they steal anything?

276
00:45:14.685 --> 00:45:16.187
They took whatever was in here.

277
00:45:16.228 --> 00:45:20.316
That? Oh. that wasn't stolen.
Was it. Dr. Stone?

278
00:45:20.441 --> 00:45:23.069
No. That was misplaced
a while ago.

279
00:45:23.152 --> 00:45:27.198
Object 6-1-9-8-2. Department
of Defense Archives.

280
00:45:27.239 --> 00:45:29.408
- Mmm-hmm.
- What was it?

281
00:45:29.533 --> 00:45:30.533
I don't know.

282
00:45:30.618 --> 00:45:31.911
You don't know?

283
00:45:32.078 --> 00:45:34.080
I don't know. which was why
I was studying it.

284
00:45:34.205 --> 00:45:35.831
What's your rank. Doctor?

285
00:45:35.956 --> 00:45:38.125
Ryan. would you. uh.
do the honors?

286
00:45:38.250 --> 00:45:39.752
- Sure. Okay.
- Thanks.

287
00:45:39.877 --> 00:45:42.380
Civilian. STARLABS
is a private contractor.

288
00:45:42.463 --> 00:45:43.589
We work for the DoD.

289
00:45:43.714 --> 00:45:46.550
We advise them on xeno-science.

290
00:45:46.634 --> 00:45:48.302
"Xeno-science"?

291
00:45:48.427 --> 00:45:50.429
Alien technology.

292
00:45:57.353 --> 00:45:59.397
For example.

293
00:45:59.522 --> 00:46:01.148
the Superman ship.

294
00:46:09.490 --> 00:46:10.783
Eight people

295
00:46:10.866 --> 00:46:12.594
never signed out
of the lab last night. Doctor.

296
00:46:12.618 --> 00:46:13.828
Cleaning staff. guards.

297
00:46:13.953 --> 00:46:16.122
a few of
your research scientists.

298
00:46:16.205 --> 00:46:17.205
They were abducted.

299
00:46:18.457 --> 00:46:19.583
Are you sure?

300
00:46:19.708 --> 00:46:22.086
Witness saw it all.
He escaped.

301
00:46:22.169 --> 00:46:25.673
He's here in quarantine now.
working on an ID sketch.

302
00:46:28.509 --> 00:46:32.972
Any idea who
or what that might be?

303
00:46:52.908 --> 00:46:55.077
The box isn't safe here.

304
00:46:57.538 --> 00:46:58.998
Victor.

305
00:46:59.081 --> 00:47:01.292
they came looking for it
at the lab.

306
00:47:01.375 --> 00:47:06.130
People were taken by some kind
of monster or something.

307
00:47:08.757 --> 00:47:10.843
You know a lot about monsters.

308
00:47:11.427 --> 00:47:12.928
don't you?

309
00:47:19.226 --> 00:47:22.021
Especially how to make 'em.

310
00:50:21.867 --> 00:50:25.746
Mayday! Mayday. mayday!

311
00:50:27.247 --> 00:50:30.709
My hull is breached.
I'm going down.

312
00:50:35.756 --> 00:50:37.800
Mayday!

313
00:50:37.925 --> 00:50:40.094
Is there anybody out there?

314
00:50:45.391 --> 00:50:46.433
Ahh!

315
00:51:20.426 --> 00:51:21.593
Whiskey.

316
00:51:30.561 --> 00:51:33.355
Tell him to respect
the storm next time.

317
00:51:42.573 --> 00:51:43.741
It's on him.

318
00:52:05.971 --> 00:52:09.516
The starry heavens above me

319
00:52:12.227 --> 00:52:15.522
<i>The mortal law within</i>

320
00:52:18.775 --> 00:52:21.862
<i>So the world appears</i>

321
00:52:24.615 --> 00:52:28.160
Through this mist of tears

322
00:52:30.913 --> 00:52:33.874
<i>There is a kingdom</i>

323
00:52:33.999 --> 00:52:36.960
<i>There is a king</i>

324
00:52:37.044 --> 00:52:39.713
<i>And he lives without</i>

325
00:52:39.838 --> 00:52:42.841
<i>And he lives within</i>

326
00:52:42.966 --> 00:52:46.011
<i>There is a kingdom</i>

327
00:52:46.136 --> 00:52:49.056
<i>There is a king</i>

328
00:52:49.181 --> 00:52:52.142
<i>There is a king</i>

329
00:52:52.226 --> 00:52:55.521
<i>And he is everything</i>

330
00:54:11.805 --> 00:54:13.682
King who would be man.

331
00:54:13.807 --> 00:54:17.269
Son of a human father
and Queen of the Seas.

332
00:54:18.020 --> 00:54:19.605
All the time I've wasted

333
00:54:19.771 --> 00:54:23.150
trying to keep the promise
I made to your mother.

334
00:54:25.110 --> 00:54:26.445
Are you finished. old man?

335
00:54:26.528 --> 00:54:28.947
You never sleep
in the same place twice.

336
00:54:29.114 --> 00:54:32.034
yet you keep coming back here.

337
00:54:33.869 --> 00:54:35.829
I like it. It's quiet.

338
00:54:35.954 --> 00:54:37.831
It's your inheritance.

339
00:54:37.956 --> 00:54:40.167
You're the rightful king
of Atlantis.

340
00:54:41.168 --> 00:54:42.461
Our people suffer.

341
00:54:42.586 --> 00:54:44.379
Your people.

342
00:54:44.504 --> 00:54:48.133
A brutal. petty.
superstitious race.

343
00:54:48.258 --> 00:54:50.427
Is the surface any different?

344
00:54:50.510 --> 00:54:52.679
Nobody calls me
King of the Surface.

345
00:54:53.805 --> 00:54:55.933
What do you want. Vulko?

346
00:54:56.016 --> 00:54:57.267
Guards near the stronghold

347
00:54:57.309 --> 00:54:58.977
have been disappearing.

348
00:54:59.061 --> 00:55:00.604
Snatchers from above.

349
00:55:00.687 --> 00:55:01.938
Talk to King Orm.

350
00:55:02.022 --> 00:55:03.440
- Your brother?
- Half-brother.

351
00:55:03.523 --> 00:55:06.902
He's trying to fan the flames
of war with the surface.

352
00:55:07.027 --> 00:55:09.613
He lies.

353
00:55:09.696 --> 00:55:11.949
The snatchers have come
from the dark place.

354
00:55:12.032 --> 00:55:14.493
They're looking for it.

355
00:55:14.576 --> 00:55:18.956
The Mother Box
our people guard is not safe.

356
00:55:19.039 --> 00:55:21.541
Go to the stronghold
of Atlantis.

357
00:55:21.667 --> 00:55:23.168
Protect the box.

358
00:55:24.044 --> 00:55:25.337
The time has come.

359
00:55:27.339 --> 00:55:29.466
Take up your mother's trident.

360
00:55:40.477 --> 00:55:44.356
You can't turn your back
on the world forever. Arthur.

361
00:55:45.148 --> 00:55:48.151
Above or below.

362
00:56:17.305 --> 00:56:19.016
DeSaad.

363
00:56:19.057 --> 00:56:23.228
DeSaad! I call to thee.

364
00:56:32.070 --> 00:56:37.242
Steppenwolf.
have you begun the conquest?

365
00:56:37.367 --> 00:56:40.412
This world is divided.

366
00:56:40.495 --> 00:56:42.080
They are a primitive species.

367
00:56:42.247 --> 00:56:44.708
Unevolved and at war
with one another.

368
00:56:44.791 --> 00:56:47.544
Too separate to be one.

369
00:56:47.586 --> 00:56:50.088
Their free will
must be ripped from them.

370
00:56:50.172 --> 00:56:52.090
like the other worlds.

371
00:56:52.174 --> 00:56:56.470
Given absolution
in one glorious belief.

372
00:56:56.595 --> 00:56:58.346
to serve him.

373
00:56:58.972 --> 00:57:01.266
The Mother Boxes?

374
00:57:01.433 --> 00:57:04.394
I have found one of the three.

375
00:57:04.478 --> 00:57:07.063
The one that woke
and called to me.

376
00:57:07.147 --> 00:57:08.607
The other two still sleep.

377
00:57:08.732 --> 00:57:12.819
but the parademons
feel their presence.

378
00:57:12.944 --> 00:57:14.404
They fly.

379
00:57:14.488 --> 00:57:17.908
they search. they take
prisoners who carry the scent.

380
00:57:17.991 --> 00:57:23.288
while I build a stronghold
in the name of his glory.

381
00:57:23.789 --> 00:57:25.665
Yes.

382
00:57:26.792 --> 00:57:30.629
Mighty Steppenwolf.

383
00:57:30.712 --> 00:57:35.383
who might have sat here
by the side of the great one.

384
00:57:37.177 --> 00:57:41.765
But undone by his self-pride.

385
00:57:42.974 --> 00:57:44.434
DeSaad...

386
00:57:45.352 --> 00:57:48.313
I fall before you.

387
00:57:48.438 --> 00:57:50.315
Let me make a plea to him

388
00:57:50.398 --> 00:57:52.317
that I may come home

389
00:57:52.484 --> 00:57:55.529
after I take this world
in his name.

390
00:57:55.654 --> 00:57:58.156
You betrayed him.

391
00:57:59.324 --> 00:58:00.951
Your own family.

392
00:58:01.034 --> 00:58:03.245
I saw my mistake.

393
00:58:03.370 --> 00:58:05.831
I slaughtered those
who sought his throne.

394
00:58:05.956 --> 00:58:11.378
You still owe the great one
50.000 more worlds.

395
00:58:12.337 --> 00:58:14.464
He will hear your plea

396
00:58:14.506 --> 00:58:16.883
when you pay your debt.

397
00:58:19.719 --> 00:58:22.889
The Mother Boxes
will be found and united.

398
00:58:23.890 --> 00:58:25.976
No protectors here.

399
00:58:26.101 --> 00:58:29.479
No Lanterns. no Kryptonian.

400
00:58:29.563 --> 00:58:33.483
This world will fall.
like all the others.

401
00:58:34.359 --> 00:58:36.319
For Darkseid.

402
00:58:39.322 --> 00:58:41.658
For Darkseid.

403
00:59:02.721 --> 00:59:04.639
You know.
I paid millions of dollars

404
00:59:04.764 --> 00:59:06.391
for this building's security.

405
00:59:06.516 --> 00:59:08.226
You got your money's worth.

406
00:59:08.351 --> 00:59:10.812
Took me almost a minute
to disable it.

407
00:59:12.272 --> 00:59:13.690
Hi there.

408
00:59:15.275 --> 00:59:16.443
A new toy?

409
00:59:17.235 --> 00:59:19.487
Prototype troop carrier.

410
00:59:21.072 --> 00:59:22.532
I once knew a man

411
00:59:22.574 --> 00:59:25.201
who would have loved to fly it.

412
00:59:25.285 --> 00:59:27.078
The best minds
at Wayne Aerospace

413
00:59:27.245 --> 00:59:28.455
couldn't make it fly.

414
00:59:29.372 --> 00:59:31.041
But you can?

415
00:59:31.124 --> 00:59:32.751
I have no choice.

416
00:59:32.834 --> 00:59:35.670
I need more range
and I need more cargo.

417
00:59:35.795 --> 00:59:37.881
I think
there's an attack coming.

418
00:59:37.964 --> 00:59:39.758
Not coming. Bruce.

419
00:59:40.425 --> 00:59:43.094
It's already here.

420
00:59:43.219 --> 00:59:44.888
From what I've learned.

421
00:59:44.930 --> 00:59:47.891
they are things
from another universe.

422
00:59:47.933 --> 00:59:50.268
They serve a dark power.

423
00:59:50.393 --> 00:59:52.187
An old power.

424
00:59:52.312 --> 00:59:53.605
What do they want?

425
00:59:53.688 --> 00:59:57.776
To invade.
To conquer.

426
00:59:57.859 --> 01:00:02.405
They came here once before.
long ago.

427
01:00:07.369 --> 01:00:09.746
<i>A great armada
appeared in the sky.</i>

428
01:00:09.829 --> 01:00:12.332
<i>laying waste
to all who opposed it.</i>

429
01:00:12.457 --> 01:00:16.795
<i>The leader of the invaders
was a being called Darkseid.</i>

430
01:00:16.878 --> 01:00:21.883
<i>A name cursed and feared
in every universe.</i>

431
01:00:22.008 --> 01:00:26.096
<i>Darkseid was met in battle
by Earth's defenders.</i>

432
01:00:26.137 --> 01:00:28.932
<i>The old gods. men...</i>

433
01:00:29.015 --> 01:00:32.477
<i>Atlanteans before
their descent into the sea...</i>

434
01:00:34.646 --> 01:00:38.650
<i>Amazons before their betrayal
and enslavement</i>

435
01:00:38.733 --> 01:00:41.277
<i>and guardians from the stars.</i>

436
01:00:41.361 --> 01:00:43.279
<i>- Their histories
- had taught them</i>

437
01:00:43.363 --> 01:00:45.073
<i>Not to trust each other.</i>

438
01:00:45.198 --> 01:00:47.284
<i>not to hope for an alliance.</i>

439
01:00:47.409 --> 01:00:49.619
<i>To fight apart.</i>

440
01:01:38.251 --> 01:01:41.296
<i>As Darkseid waged war on Earth.</i>

441
01:01:41.421 --> 01:01:42.756
<i>he found a secret there.</i>

442
01:01:42.881 --> 01:01:46.676
<i>A power hidden
in the infinity of space.</i>

443
01:01:46.760 --> 01:01:48.261
<i>He called forth mystics</i>

444
01:01:48.386 --> 01:01:51.681
<i>who worshipped and controlled
three objects...</i>

445
01:01:51.765 --> 01:01:53.183
<i>the Mother Boxes.</i>

446
01:01:53.266 --> 01:01:54.851
Wait. wait. wait.

447
01:01:54.934 --> 01:01:55.727
"Mother Boxes"?

448
01:01:55.894 --> 01:01:58.980
Indestructible living machines.

449
01:01:59.105 --> 01:02:01.941
<i>made from a science so advanced.</i>

450
01:02:02.067 --> 01:02:04.069
<i>it looks like sorcery.</i>

451
01:02:04.152 --> 01:02:05.529
<i>To conquer. three boxes</i>

452
01:02:05.530 --> 01:02:06.905
<i>have to synchronize</i>

453
01:02:06.988 --> 01:02:10.200
<i>and join together
into The Unity.</i>

454
01:02:10.283 --> 01:02:13.411
<i>The Unity cleanses
a planet with fire.</i>

455
01:02:13.495 --> 01:02:17.207
<i>transforming it into a copy
of the enemy's world.</i>

456
01:02:17.290 --> 01:02:21.127
<i>All who live
become servants of Darkseid.</i>

457
01:02:21.252 --> 01:02:24.214
<i>Alive but drained of life.</i>

458
01:02:24.297 --> 01:02:25.799
<i>Parademons.</i>

459
01:02:26.841 --> 01:02:29.010
Amazons!

460
01:02:34.933 --> 01:02:36.476
With me!

461
01:03:05.797 --> 01:03:08.424
<i>But before The Unity
could synchronize.</i>

462
01:03:08.508 --> 01:03:10.468
<i>the defenders of Earth attacked</i>

463
01:03:10.635 --> 01:03:12.345
<i>and fought as one.</i>

464
01:03:12.470 --> 01:03:15.515
<i>Amazons alongside Atlanteans.</i>

465
01:03:15.640 --> 01:03:17.142
<i>Zeus and his son Ares</i>

466
01:03:17.267 --> 01:03:20.937
<i>alongside the guardians
from the sky.</i>

467
01:03:21.020 --> 01:03:24.274
<i>A golden Age of Heroes
fighting together</i>

468
01:03:24.399 --> 01:03:25.942
<i>to defend life on Earth.</i>

469
01:05:22.308 --> 01:05:25.144
<i>They did what no world
had ever done.</i>

470
01:05:25.270 --> 01:05:27.605
<i>Sent the enemies
back into the stars.</i>

471
01:05:30.024 --> 01:05:33.778
<i>The three Mother Boxes
never synchronized.</i>

472
01:05:33.945 --> 01:05:35.614
-The Unity never came to pass.

473
01:05:37.407 --> 01:05:39.951
<i>But. in their retreat.</i>

474
01:05:40.076 --> 01:05:43.162
<i>the boxes were left behind
on Earth.</i>

475
01:05:43.288 --> 01:05:47.250
<i>They grew weak.
Dogs without masters</i>

476
01:05:49.127 --> 01:05:50.628
<i>falling asleep.</i>

477
01:05:50.753 --> 01:05:53.131
<i>awaiting their return.</i>

478
01:05:53.256 --> 01:05:55.758
<i>Fading from the view
of the enemy.</i>

479
01:05:55.800 --> 01:05:59.137
<i>anonymous
among a trillion worlds.</i>

480
01:06:15.903 --> 01:06:19.449
<i>The defenders of Earth
made a vow.</i>

481
01:06:19.490 --> 01:06:22.785
<i>Men. Atlanteans. and Amazons.</i>

482
01:06:22.827 --> 01:06:24.704
<i>Each would enshrine and guard</i>

483
01:06:24.829 --> 01:06:26.623
<i>one of the three
sleeping Mother Boxes</i>

484
01:06:26.706 --> 01:06:30.501
<i>according to the rites
and rituals of their culture</i>

485
01:06:30.668 --> 01:06:33.171
<i>in case a box
should ever wake again</i>

486
01:06:33.338 --> 01:06:35.214
<i>to call out
to the planet Apokolips</i>

487
01:06:35.340 --> 01:06:37.008
<i>to return and conquer</i>

488
01:06:37.091 --> 01:06:41.095
<i>the only world
Darkseid had ever lost.</i>

489
01:07:56.921 --> 01:08:00.049
Something woke the box
my people guard.

490
01:08:00.174 --> 01:08:02.218
It called out
to the dark place...

491
01:08:02.343 --> 01:08:05.054
to one of Darkseid's conquerors.

492
01:08:05.805 --> 01:08:08.057
The enemy is here.

493
01:08:08.141 --> 01:08:09.892
If he's here. where is he?

494
01:08:09.976 --> 01:08:12.103
He'll be searching
for the other two boxes.

495
01:08:12.228 --> 01:08:15.231
Hiding until he has all three.
Until he's ready.

496
01:08:15.314 --> 01:08:19.694
Then we have to be ready.
You. me. the others.

497
01:08:19.819 --> 01:08:22.905
They said the Age of Heroes
would never come again.

498
01:08:22.947 --> 01:08:24.574
No. it will.

499
01:08:24.657 --> 01:08:26.409
It has to.

500
01:08:28.035 --> 01:08:31.789
The others.
Where are they?

501
01:08:53.686 --> 01:08:54.686
Am I late?

502
01:08:54.812 --> 01:08:57.315
No. I'm so late.
I'm very late.

503
01:08:57.398 --> 01:08:58.900
Oh. hey. buddy. Hey.

504
01:08:59.025 --> 01:09:00.776
Oh. No.

505
01:09:00.860 --> 01:09:03.821
Okay. bye. Okay.

506
01:09:03.946 --> 01:09:06.324
I'm so sorry.

507
01:09:06.407 --> 01:09:07.784
I'm late.

508
01:09:13.039 --> 01:09:14.457
- Are you. uh...
- I'm...

509
01:09:14.540 --> 01:09:16.518
I'm so sorry I'm so late.
I didn't mean to be so late.

510
01:09:16.542 --> 01:09:18.187
I'm me and I'm here
and I'm so sorry I'm late.

511
01:09:18.211 --> 01:09:19.504
Essentially.
the bus didn't come.

512
01:09:19.670 --> 01:09:20.797
then the bus did come.

513
01:09:20.880 --> 01:09:21.940
but then there was
this old woman

514
01:09:21.964 --> 01:09:23.132
counting change for the fare.

515
01:09:23.216 --> 01:09:24.576
like. nickel. penny.
nickel. penny.

516
01:09:24.675 --> 01:09:26.435
Like. jeez Louise.
let this woman on the bus.

517
01:09:26.469 --> 01:09:27.595
She's 107 years old.

518
01:09:27.762 --> 01:09:29.406
these are some of her
last few moments of life.

519
01:09:29.430 --> 01:09:30.723
Resume.

520
01:09:30.848 --> 01:09:31.849
Resume.

521
01:09:35.019 --> 01:09:37.021
Come on.

522
01:09:39.565 --> 01:09:40.650
Come on.

523
01:09:40.775 --> 01:09:42.318
From the French. of course.

524
01:09:42.360 --> 01:09:45.530
<i>"Resume."</i> I believe.
is a past participle of...

525
01:09:50.952 --> 01:09:52.620
Uh. wow. That's no good.

526
01:09:52.745 --> 01:09:54.385
It's like. what lives
in my pocket. right?

527
01:09:54.497 --> 01:09:57.333
